reviews.text: Come with my friend today for lunch, very yummy foods! English beef stew and rice is so good. Wine or bottle beer is included with the set.  Price is worth. Cozy environment for a break in lunch time.

The food is pretty good, but the service is terrific. Every staff member seems to enjoy their job. Small but cosy; really quick to get food to table. If you like pizza with ultra thin crispy crust then you'll like it here.
Nice staff! Good for happy hour! Pizza is tasty!

I travelled around Hong Kong for hours trying to find a good friendly place to drink. I arrived here little less then an hour ago, and it's the best place I've had a drink so far. Staff are super friendly, and Im drinking during happy hour which is BOGOF. Currently on my second Hoegaarden which means I got two 50cl drinks for 4pound each. Fantastic 👌(perfect remedy to being stuck in poor weather)
Was a great stay there the staff very very good

result.name: Peninsula Centre Arcade

reviews.text: An old mall partly renovated.  Tenants kept on changing.  Small shops were the majority.

Good Location but Old Shopping plaza.
The shopping centre is getting old and the stores does not look very attractive.  However, if you travel by MTR, you can tap on a saving check point.  It can save you $2 if you start your next ride at Tsim Sha Tsui or Tsim Sha Tsui East MTR station.

There is a really weird fountain in the middle so if someone dropped something, they wouldn’t be able to get it back because it would fall down about 20 metres and then break on some tiles. Not good shops, very bad look from outside and inside, very dirty even though there are cleaners there. Would NOT want to go there ever again if I could.
good shops, affordable goods, tailors, massage and other facilities that save time
Old mall at tsim she Tsui
